  "text": "It has been proposed that the manipulation of the boiling point of the solvents that are confined in the nanopores could be exploited as a drug delivery system. Below the 2-nm pore radius, the boiling point of water is significantly lower compared to the bulk. At the appropriate temperature, water in the confined space will, therefore, undergo phase transition to form gas, and this will expel the content from the tube lumina. The combination of the different solvents such as water and carbon dioxide under nanoconfinement could provide interesting pressure-activated devices. Heat, light, or electrical conduction could serve to induce the phase transition as the driving force for drug expulsion [CITATION_1] .",
